      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix Antigravity summary bar ignoring Gemini family quota by masking it with untracked Claude quota",
        "body": "Resolves #1334. \n\nIn Antigravity Status Probe, an untracked model quota without a `remainingFraction` was defaulting to `0` for `remainingPercent`, thereby yielding `100` for `usedPercent`. When automatic summary mode picks the most constrained window across primary/secondary/tertiary lanes, an untracked Claude quota (yielding 100% used) could incorrectly mask an actually exhausted Gemini quota, causing the summary bar to perpetually show 100%. \n\nThis PR defaults `remainingPercent` to `100` for `nil` remaining fractions to prevent them from surfacing as exhausted quota.",
